The paper deals with approximation algorithms for maximizing monotone submodular functions, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science. The paper introduces a novel approach based on discrete convexity, which is a topic closely related to discrete optimization and combinatorial geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
